                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>On March 9, 1951, Mr. Dulles testified before the Senate Foreign Relations
                    Committee, meeting in Executive Session, on issues involved in the negotiation
                    of the Japanese Peace Treaty. For transcript of this testimony, see <hi
                        rend="italic">Executive Sessions of the Senate Foreign Relations
                        Committee</hi> (<hi rend="italic">Historical Series</hi>), <ref
                        target="frus1951v03p1#pg_259">volume III, part 1, 82d Congress, 1 Session,
                        1951 (Washington: Government Printing Office, 1976), pages 259</ref>–<ref
                        target="frus1951v03p1#pg_297">297</ref>.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
